-- Xylem Wins Brazil Wastewater Treatment Plant Technology Contract
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-09-26T11:10:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-26/xylem-wins-brazil-wastewater-treatment-plant-technology-contract.html
Xylem Inc., the water technology
company spun off from  ITT Corp. (ITT)  last year, won a wastewater
treatment plant supply contract in  Brazil .  The White Plains, N.Y.-based company gave no terms for the
sewage plant contract to supply treatment technology and systems
that will serve 60,000 people in Campo Grande in the Mato Grosso
state of Brazil.  The contract for the Imbirussu wastewater plant was awarded
by Aguas Guariroba, part of the Equipav group, Xylem said in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
